One man died and two others sustained injuries after three vehicles collided at the Columbine and Main Road intersection in Mondeor on Saturday.On arrival ER24 paramedics found one light motor vehicle lying on its roof in the middle of the road while two others were found parked nearby.On closer inspection, paramedics found two men lying trapped inside the overturned vehicle.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics found that the passenger had sustained numerous, fatal injuries. Nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene.He added: &#8220;The driver was found lying trapped and to be in a critical condition. Rescue services had to use the jaws-of-life equipment to free the man from the vehicle. Once freed, paramedics treated him and provided him with advanced life support interventions&#8221;.The cause of the collision is not yet known-TNA Reporter